    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="617" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.
                                (Received May 2.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my note of the 14th
                            ultimo, respecting hostilities in Samoa, I have now the honor to inform
                            you, in accordance with instructions from the Earl of Kimberley, that
                            Her Majesty’s consul at Apia reported by telegraph on the 27th of March
                            last that he has still hopes that peace may be restored in Samoa, and
                            that he does not share the anxiety felt by his United States
                            colleague.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
